Plotex (this fork) — primary author
-----------------------------------
M. Ignacio Monge García <monge.ignacio@gmail.com>
   https://github.com/IgnacioMonge/plotex

Plotex was forked from Veusz 4.2 in 2026 and adds new plot types
(Kaplan-Meier, ROC, Bland-Altman, violin, pie, Pareto, QQ, ridgeline,
heatmaps, polar trending, bracket annotations), a modernized ribbon UI,
12+ plot themes, scientific color palettes, hardened safe-mode and
loader, and an extensive regression test suite.


Upstream Veusz — original authors
---------------------------------
Jeremy Sanders <jeremy@jeremysanders.net>
   http://www.jeremysanders.net/
James Graham <jg307@cam.ac.uk>

Plotex is built on the foundation of Veusz; the work of Jeremy Sanders
and every Veusz contributor is gratefully acknowledged. See
ChangeLog.veusz-upstream for the original Veusz changelog.
